patch.description:
This partially updates the contact with fields you specify in the request. The properties that are not in the request, won't be updated and stay the same, you update only those fields, that present in the input contact object in the body of your request. You can specify one or multiple properties.

### Request headers:
```
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {auth_token}
x-api-key: {api_key}
```
### Response headers:
```
Content-Type: application/json
```

The common request body format is as follows:
```javascript
{
"firstName":"new first name",
"lastName":"new last name",
"patronymic":"new middle name",
"comment":"new comment",
"tags":[
    //new array of tags
],
"channels":[
    //new array of channels
]}
```
#Example 1 - update first name and last name only:
```javascript
{
    "firstName":"new first name",
    "lastName":"new last name",
}
```
#Example 2 - update comment and replace all tags by the new  one: "my-new-tag":
```javascript
{
    "comment":"my new comment",
    "tags":["my-new-tag"]
}
```

